text: Morgan Hill State Forest is a state forest in Onondaga County and Cortland County, New York, United States. It includes of hiking trails and of public forest access roads. The hiking trails are part of the main North Country Trail and Onondaga Branch of the Finger Lakes Trail. ==References== ==External links== * Map and photographs of the state forest's trail system.
